---
const calendarUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_CALENDAR_URL?.trim() || "https://cal.com/chaiwithjai/ai-guidance-counselor";
---
<!doctype html>
<html data-wf-domain="dharmicdata.org" lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>About Jai Bhagat | Dharmic Data</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Why Jai Bhagat is turning years of software work and free economic empowerment teaching into a public AI practice and a future collective." />
    <meta property="og:title" content="About Jai Bhagat | Dharmic Data" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="The work, choices, and June 2027 path behind Dharmic Data." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <link href="/assets/webflow-bundle/c36a0562fb6b95e9.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webfont.js"></script>
    <script is:inline>WebFont.load({google:{families:["Fredoka:300,400,500,600,700","Inter:300,400,500,600,700"]}});</script>
    <link href="/dharmic-assets/shakti-seva-mark.svg" rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <link href="/dharmic-treatment.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link href="/template-about.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body class="dharmic-about">
    <a class="dharmic-skip" href="#main">Skip to main content</a>
    <div class="page-wrapper">
      <header class="navbar w-nav" data-collapse="medium" data-duration="400" role="banner">
        <div class="navbar-wrapper">
          <a href="/" class="navbar-brand w-nav-brand"><img src="/dharmic-assets/dharmic-data-logo.svg" alt="Dharmic Data" class="nav-logo black" /></a>
          <nav class="menu-wrapper w-nav-menu" role="navigation">
            <div class="menu-items">
              <a href="/" class="nav-link">Home</a>
              <a href="/about" aria-current="page" class="nav-link w--current">About</a>
              <a href="/#projects" class="nav-link">Projects</a>
              <a href="/vlog" class="nav-link">Technical vlog</a>
            </div>
          </nav>
          <div class="nav-buttons desk"><a href={calendarUrl} class="primary-button w-inline-block"><div class="button-texts"><div class="button-text _01">Book AI guidance</div><div class="button-text _02">Book AI guidance</div></div></a></div>
          <div class="menu-button w-nav-button"><div class="menu-text _01">Menu</div><div class="menu-text _02">Cancel</div></div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main id="main">
        <section class="about-template-hero">
          <div class="about-template-copy">
            <p class="subtitle">The person behind the public work</p>
            <h1><span>Software</span> <span class="sticker green">Teacher</span> <span>Public</span> <span class="sticker coral">Builder</span></h1>
            <p class="about-template-lead">Hi, I'm Jai Bhagat. I help people find one useful AI project, test it against real work, and learn enough to make the next decision for themselves.</p>
            <div class="about-template-actions"><a href={calendarUrl} class="primary-button about-primary">Book AI guidance · $125</a><a href="#story" class="about-text-link">Why I am building this</a></div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-character-stage">
            <div class="about-character-rive" data-rive-url="/assets/cdn/69577d21-6995b79cfaa7bf474085d59c_home_page_character_1-1-.riv" data-rive-state-machine="State Machine 1" data-rive-artboard="Artboard" data-rive-autoplay="true" data-rive-fit="cover" data-rive-alignment="center" data-animation-type="rive"><canvas></canvas></div>
            <span class="about-note note-top">Start with the person</span>
            <span class="about-note note-bottom">Show the proof</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-proof-rail" aria-label="Experience and teaching proof">
          <div class="proof-pill pink"><strong>10+ years</strong><span>software and teaching</span></div>
          <div class="proof-pill blue"><strong>4.9 / 5.0</strong><span>instructor rating</span></div>
          <div class="proof-pill orange"><strong>HashiCorp</strong><span>production engineering</span></div>
          <div class="proof-pill green"><strong>Parsons</strong><span>adult instruction</span></div>
        </section>

        <section id="story" class="about-story">
          <div class="about-story-heading">
            <p class="subtitle white">The honest version</p>
            <h2>This is the<br><span class="sticker yellow">in-between</span><br>period.</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="about-story-copy">
            <p class="story-big">For years, I taught economic empowerment work for free. I am now turning that practice into a public effort that can last beyond my calendar.</p>
            <p>Dharmic Data is not a nonprofit today. Between now and June 2027, paid sessions support the time to publish working demos, document what succeeds and fails, and learn what a future collective should become.</p>
            <p>I have spent more than ten years moving between software and teaching. I shipped production software at HashiCorp, taught JavaScript at Parsons, and helped Queens founders and operators use AI in work they already care about.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="about-photo-stack" aria-label="Photos of Jai teaching and building">
            <img class="photo-main" src="/dharmic-assets/jai-studio.jpg" alt="Jai speaking about making a useful project with AI" />
            <img class="photo-card" src="/dharmic-assets/jai-dogged-pursuits.jpg" alt="Dogged Pursuits photo strip showing Jai teaching and breathing" />
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-choices">
          <header class="about-section-heading">
            <p class="subtitle">What makes the work different</p>
            <h2>Choose the <span class="sticker blue">job</span><br>before the <span class="sticker green">tool</span>.</h2>
            <p>I pursue AI when it gives a person more control over useful work. I pass when a simpler system is safer or clearer.</p>
          </header>
          <ol class="choice-grid">
            <li class="pink"><span>01</span><h3>Start with real work</h3><p>Name the recurring problem before choosing a model.</p></li>
            <li class="blue"><span>02</span><h3>Use real constraints</h3><p>Test against the files, repository, data, time, and machine that actually matter.</p></li>
            <li class="orange"><span>03</span><h3>Set the boundary</h3><p>Decide what the model may read and which choices always need review.</p></li>
            <li class="green"><span>04</span><h3>Make one small test</h3><p>Measure one useful task before expanding the system.</p></li>
            <li class="coral"><span>05</span><h3>Publish the proof</h3><p>Show sources, traces, evaluations, limits, and failed attempts.</p></li>
            <li class="yellow"><span>06</span><h3>Know when to pass</h3><p>Use ordinary code or a person when AI is not the right tool.</p></li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="about-shakti">
          <div class="shakti-window"><img src="/dharmic-assets/shakti-live-result.png" alt="Shakti showing a New York City building record" /><span>LIVE PUBLIC CASE STUDY</span></div>
          <div class="shakti-copy"><p class="subtitle white">Proof, not a promise</p><h2>Shakti shows the method in public.</h2><p>Its public housing lookup uses ordinary code, not AI. It shows City sources, protects unit details, and makes the address match visible. The optional local AI explains a treated packet but cannot change the record or next step.</p><div class="about-template-actions"><a href="https://shakti.dharmicdata.org" class="primary-button about-light">Try Shakti</a><a href="https://github.com/ChaiWithJai/shakti-seva-studio" class="about-text-link light">Inspect the evidence</a></div></div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-roadmap">
          <div class="roadmap-intro"><p class="subtitle">Now through June 2027</p><h2>Paid guidance<br><span class="sticker coral">seeds</span> the<br>public work.</h2><p>The goal is a model where useful teaching and open projects support each other.</p></div>
          <ol class="roadmap-list">
            <li><span>Now</span><strong>Rent the calendar</strong><p>One-to-one guidance pays for time to teach, build, and publish.</p></li>
            <li><span>Next</span><strong>Test small learning rooms</strong><p>Private cohorts, short courses, and a Dogged Pursuits practice room may run with clear, modest promises. They are not for sale yet.</p></li>
            <li><span>June 2027</span><strong>Seed the collective</strong><p>Use the evidence from this period to shape a nonprofit collective for public demos, practical teaching, and shared methods.</p></li>
          </ol>
          <div class="roadmap-rive" data-rive-url="/assets/cdn/69577d21-6995b79cd68776d3c9ca5a07_home-page-bowl-charater-2-1-.riv" data-rive-state-machine="State Machine 1" data-rive-artboard="Artboard" data-rive-autoplay="true" data-rive-fit="cover" data-rive-alignment="center" data-animation-type="rive"><canvas></canvas></div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-offer">
          <div><p class="subtitle">The offer today</p><h2>Bring one real problem.<br>Leave with a <span class="sticker blue">test</span> you can run.</h2><p>In 60 minutes, we define a use case, choose a tool, set data boundaries, and write a 30 day test plan.</p><a href={calendarUrl} class="primary-button about-primary">Book AI guidance · $125</a></div>
          <aside><p class="subtitle">AI Guidance Counselor</p><strong>$125</strong><span>60 minutes</span><ul><li>A defined first use case</li><li>A tool or subscription choice</li><li>Clear data and action boundaries</li><li>A written 30 day test</li></ul><p class="offer-limit">Guidance and project definition. This is not a promise of a finished software build.</p></aside>
        </section>

        <section class="about-final">
          <div class="about-final-copy"><p class="subtitle">Keep exploring</p><h2>See the <span class="sticker yellow">work</span>,<br>then decide.</h2><div class="about-template-actions"><a href="/" class="primary-button about-primary">Back to the homepage</a><a href="/vlog" class="about-text-link">Read the build stories</a></div></div>
          <div class="footer-rive desk" data-rive-url="/assets/cdn/69577d21-6995b79cb5c877d98300cec7_footer-bowl-character-animation-3.riv" data-rive-state-machine="State Machine 1" data-rive-artboard="Artboard" data-rive-autoplay="true" data-rive-fit="contain" data-rive-alignment="center" data-animation-type="rive"><canvas></canvas></div>
        </section>
      </main>

      <footer class="about-footer"><img src="/dharmic-assets/dharmic-data-logo.svg" alt="Dharmic Data" /><p>Independent project. Working toward a nonprofit collective. Not a registered nonprofit today.</p><nav><a href="/">Home</a><a href="/vlog">Technical vlog</a><a href="https://github.com/ChaiWithJai/dharmic-data">Source</a></nav></footer>
    </div>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/jquery-3.5.1.min.dc5e7f18c8.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webflow.schunk.7a4a7f019cc01602.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webflow.schunk.90febbc43c629f61.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webflow.73431be6.2c71108c00d371a3.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
